		<td><b>Arguments vs Parameters</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I just learned that Arguments and Parameters are not the same thing.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">void foo(int x, int y, int z)&nbsp; // &lt;- Parameters x, y, z<br />{<br /><br />}<br /><br />void main()<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; int a, b, c;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; foo(a, b, c);&nbsp; // &lt;- arguments a, b, c<br />}<br /></div><br />Parameters are what the function specifies, and arguments are what you are passing in.<br /><br />So what other programming terminology have you been using completely wrong?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


