	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Parameters are what the function specifies, and arguments are what you are passing in.</div><br />Although one can safely use one or the other in most situations (unless you're taking a CS exam where the purpose is to demonstrate that you've understood the difference, it doesn't really matter). You'll also find people referring to them as formal parameters and actual parameters, or in some cases formal arguments and actual arguments.

		

		</td>
